overview:
Diane Keng is one of the co-founders and marketing director of MyWEBoo Inc.

She is currently a high school senior. A year and a half ago, she and her brother, Steven Keng, founded MyWEBoo Inc. He handled the technical and organizational activities and she handled the marketing and promotions. This is her 3rd start-up. Her prior two included a tshirt screen printing business and a teen market research firm. However due to SATS, ACTS, AP testing, Finals, and of course other extracurriculers, both did not see to full fruition.

Since freshman year, she was part of DECA, an association of marketing students. As a junior, she was the Silicon Valley DECA President. As a senior, she was elected the California DECA State President. Her term ended in March and she has been working full-time on MyWEBoo (other than school).
